## Mockery Cheat Sheet

### Setup Mock Expectations

| Pattern | Usage |
|---------|-------|
| `.once()` | Called exactly 1x |
| `.twice()` | Called exactly 2x |
| `.times(n)` | Called exactly n times |
| `.atLeast()->once()` | Called at least 1x |
| `.never()` | Should not be called |

### Return Values

```php
// Single return value
->andReturn($value)

// Multiple sequential returns
->andReturn($value1)->andReturn($value2)

// Throw exception
->andThrow(new Exception("Error"))

// Callback for complex logic
->andReturnUsing(fn($arg) => process($arg))
```

### Argument Matching

```php
// Exact match
->with("exact_value")

// Type checking
->with(Mockery::type('string'), Mockery::type('array'))

// Callback validation
->with(Mockery::on(fn($arg) => $arg['key'] === 'value'))

// Any argument
->with(Mockery::any())

// Ignore additional arguments
->withArgs([$arg1, $arg2])
```

### Full Mock Expression

```php
$this->service->shouldReceive('method')
    ->once()
    ->with("ARG1", Mockery::type('array'))
    ->andReturn($value);
```

