## Anti-Patterns ❌

```php
// ❌ DON'T: Hardcoded numbers without explanation
if ($count > 5) { }

// ✅ DO: Use named constants
const MINIMUM_RECORDS = 5;
if ($count >= self::MINIMUM_RECORDS) { }

// ❌ DON'T: Test interdependencies
public function testA() { /* sets up data for testB */ }
public function testB() { /* depends on testA */ }

// ✅ DO: Each test is independent
// Both setUp() and helper methods handle setup

// ❌ DON'T: Call real services
$result = new RealDatabaseService()->fetch();

// ✅ DO: Mock external dependencies
$this->db->shouldReceive('fetch')->andReturn($data);

// ❌ DON'T: Test implementation details
$this->assertEquals($object->privateVar, 'value');

// ✅ DO: Test behavior/output
$this->assertEquals($expectedResult, $method());

// ❌ DON'T: Multiple assertions testing different things
public function testMultipleThings() {
    $this->assertTrue($a);
    $this->assertFalse($b);
    $this->assertEquals($c, $d);
}

// ✅ DO: One assertion per logical thing (or related group)
public function testReturnsTrue() { $this->assertTrue($result); }
public function testSetsValueCorrectly() { $this->assertEquals($expected, $result); }
```

